      <h4>Learning Time Terms</h4>
      <p>Read the three time terms below to your protege.  Ask your protege if they have any questions regarding the definitions</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p> <span class="toBold">Committed Time -</span>This time is related to your short-term and long-term goals and is associated with what you value most.  (i.e. school, family, studying, exercise)</p>
          <p><span class="toBold">Maintenance Time - </span>This is the time you spend taking care of yourself.  (i.e. eating, sleeping, showering, getting dressed)</p>
          <p><span class="toBold">Discretionary Time - </span>This is considered the “free” time you spend on the things you value most in your life.  It should align with your committed time and focuses on your mental, physical and spiritual well-being.   ( i.e. hobbies, church, talking with friends)</p>

        </li>
      </ul>

